# Dialogue Varieties
Title: Dialogue Varieties

## Dramatis Personae

ALICE - The main speaker
BOB/ROBERT - Her friend
CHARLIE - A bystander

## ACT I

### SCENE 1

// Simple single-line dialogue
ALICE
Hello.

// Multi-line dialogue
BOB
Hello there, Alice.
It is good to see you again.
I have been away for quite some time.

// Dialogue with parenthetical after character name
CHARLIE
(whispering)
Who are those people?

// Dialogue with inline stage directions
ALICE
I can't believe (turning to BOB) you're actually here.

// Dialogue with verse (indented lines)
BOB
Let me tell you what I saw:
  A ship upon the morning sea,
  its sails unfurled and running free,
  against a sky of gold and grey.

// Multiple characters in quick sequence
ALICE
What happened next?

BOB
It vanished.

CHARLIE
Impossible.

ALICE
Nothing is impossible.

// Forced character name with @
@CHARLIE
I suppose you are right.

// Character with alias speaking
ROBERT
Please, call me Robert when we are in public.

// Multi-line with mixed verse and prose
ALICE
That reminds me of what my mother used to say:
  The world is wide and full of woe,
  but love will find a way.
She was always like that. Poetic at the worst times.
